title: White House Contradicts Justice Department on Immigration Order - WSJ
text:
Politics White House Contradicts Justice Department on Immigration Order Government may take different path than the one the Justice Department told a federal court it would take By @brkend Feb. 21, 2017 9:44 p.m. ET 
White House press secretary Sean Spicer on Tuesday contradicted a Justice Department court filing on President Donald Trump’s plans to rescind his executive order on visas and refugees, saying the original ban wouldn’t be revoked as another one is issued. 
At a White House press briefing, Mr. Spicer said the president would soon issue a new executive order with an updated iteration of the ban but he wouldn’t rescind the current order, which has been suspended by the courts.
